    }
    iRun <- Vectorize(iRun, "i")

    library(parallel)
    cc <- makeCluster(detectCores()-1)
    clusterExport(cc, c("trainSet", "seedvec", "seqBoot"))
    i_sB <- tryCatch(parLapply(cc, 1:200, iRun), error=function(e) NA, warning=function(w) NA)
    clusterEvalQ(cc, {gc()})
    stopCluster(cc)

    sBmat <- NULL
    for(i in 1:200)
    {
      sBmat <- cbind(sBmat, i_sB[[i]])
    }
    write.csv(sBmat, "~/Dropbox/Teaching/STAT430/homework/hw03/sBmat.csv", row.names = F)
  }

  #########################################
  # bagging based on sequential bootstrap #
  #########################################
  sBmat <- read.csv("~/Dropbox/Teaching/STAT430/homework/hw03/sBmat.csv", header = T)
  nTrain <- nrow(trainSet)
  nTest <- nrow(testSet)
  OOBpred <- matrix(0, nTrain, 200)
  Testpred <- matrix(0, nTest, 200)
 
  for(i in 1:200)
  {
    oob <- setdiff(1:nTrain, unique(sBmat[,i]))
    i_fit <- rpart(Y ~ C + V, data = trainSet[sBmat[,i],])
    pred <- predict(i_fit, newdata = trainSet[oob,], type="class")
    OOBpred[oob, i] <- ifelse(pred=="1",1,-1)
    pred <- predict(i_fit, newdata = testSet, type="class")
    Testpred[, i] <- ifelse(pred=="1",1,-1)
  }
 
  predOOB <- ifelse(apply(OOBpred,1,sum)<=0, "0","1")
  table(observed = trainSet$Y, predicted = predOOB)

  Testprob <- Testvote / apply(Testvote,1,sum) # prob of "0" and "1" (first col is "0")
  classes <- levels(datEva$Y)

    auc_perf <- performance(pred, measure = "auc")

  }

    OOBpred[oob, i] <- ifelse(pred=="1",1,-1)
